    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "Shows the Sender/Recipient Mailaddress in the Mail List. Normaly, only the Name is displayed, which is wrong on most Spam Mails. Now you also can clearly see which of your Mail Addresses was used, extremly usefull if you are using a chatch-all feature on your Mailserver.\nBased on G. Gersdorfs \"Show InOut\"! Translated into Hungarian and bugfixed by Mikes Kaszmán István. Translated intoItalian by Underpass. Thanks for your Support!"
    },
    "developer_comments": {
        "en-US": "As mentioned in the version notes, sorting is not possible when using Thunderbird in a version below 2. In TB 2 a completely different mechanism is used to create the columns. This also will fix the problem, that sometimes the columns can not be resized!\nAs it will be a lot work to fix those problems in TB 1.5, I hope you can wait till TB 2 is final, which should be within the first quarter of 2007.\n\nPlease also have a look at my homepage for the current version:\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/7ce1336d3ca2b1723494ddeef583aa995762df16a8ae408b34f03e2fa90100e3/http%3A//www.moritz-abraham.de/en/programme/show-address.html\">http://www.moritz-abraham.de/en/programme/show-address.html</a>"
    },
